Yenagoa – Governor Douye Diri of Bayelsa State has congratulated the management, players and technical crew of Bayelsa Queens Football Club for winning the 2021/2022 Nigerian Women Football League (NWFL). The team beat five other rivals in the NWFL Super Six Championship, which ended on Sunday in Benin City, the Edo State capital. Diri described their unbeaten run at the championship as a manifestation of the fact that their brilliant performance during the regular season was not a fluke. -Advertisement- He stated in a statement issued on Monday by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr. Daniel Alabrah that Bayelsa Queens did not just emerge champions, but that they also put up one of the best overall performances in the history of the competition as they won all their five matches to amass a total of 15 points. Also, a member of the team, Gift Monday, won the top scorer award after scoring 12 goals, while the team’s goalkeeper, Gabrielle Ange Bawou, won the best goalkeeper award. The governor attributed their brilliant performance to hard work, commitment and focus on the part of the management, the coaches and the players. He also commended the Aisha Falode-led NWFL Board for organising what he described as a hitch-free competition that produced true and worthy champions in Bayelsa Queens.